Class BinaryKeysetReader

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.google.crypto.tink.BinaryKeysetReader
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    KeysetReader

    public final class BinaryKeysetReader
extends Object
implements KeysetReader
    A KeysetReader that can read from some source cleartext or encrypted keysets in proto binary wire format.

    1.0.0

        public static KeysetReader withInputStream(InputStream stream)
        Static method to create a BinaryKeysetReader from an InputStream.

        Note: the input stream won't be read until read() or readEncrypted() is called, and will be closed immediately after the keyset is read.
